modules.description: This module defines command-line interface terms for selecting PKCS#11 slots, tokens, and authentication parameters. It provides predefined terms for parsing command-line arguments related to slot index, ID, description, token label, PIN, load mode, and user type, ensuring correct value conversion and option handling. These terms are used to build CLI commands that interact with PKCS#11 cryptographic devices, such as selecting a specific token or authenticating a user.

This module defines command-line arguments and converters for selecting PKCS#11 slots, tokens, and library loading options. It provides typed values for slot index, ID, description, token label, DLL path, PIN, load mode, and user type, all as optional Cmdliner arguments. These are used directly in command-line parsing to configure PKCS#11 session parameters and library interaction behavior.

This module provides command-line argument definitions and parsing terms for configuring PKCS#11 session parameters. It works with string, integer, and custom types representing slot identifiers, token labels, library paths, PINs, and user types. Concrete use cases include selecting a PKCS#11 slot by index or description, specifying a token label for authentication, and loading a PKCS#11 library with a given path and mode.
